<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 08 at 3:54AM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...CAUTIOUS TRAVEL IS ADVISED FOR SNOW-COVERED ROADWAYS THIS
MORNING...
Light but persistent lake enhanced snow has resulted in a dusting
to around a half-inch of accumulation overnight. Additional light
accumulation will remain possible through 6 AM. Light snow is not
expected to cause any major reductions in visibility.
&amp;&amp;
PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...
* The combination of light snow and cold temperatures will result
in slippery conditions and variable traffic rates. Motorists
are urged to use caution and account for the variable driving
conditions by allowing extra time.
* Prepare, plan and stay informed. Visit http://go.usa.gov/c7kkP</description>
